33:22.125 --> 33:24.043
You're my oldest,

33:24.043 --> 33:26.045
best friend.

33:28.006 --> 33:30.049
What'll I do without you?

33:38.016 --> 33:41.477
Charles? We should do this.

33:50.278 --> 33:52.739
She was right here.

34:00.413 --> 34:03.041
Hey. Look at this.

34:05.084 --> 34:07.754
Did she write a message with her blood?

34:09.005 --> 34:11.424
Charles, do you know what that means?

34:13.092 --> 34:14.594
Yes.

34:15.386 --> 34:16.679
I do.

34:18.222 --> 34:21.517
<i>Another thing my father taught me.
If you wanna have a long career,</i>

34:21.517 --> 34:24.062
<i>you need to find your person.</i>

34:24.604 --> 34:26.397
<i>Your number one.</i>

34:26.397 --> 34:29.025
The one you always fall for.

34:29.025 --> 34:31.277
And the day I met Charles-Haden Savage,

34:32.487 --> 34:34.405
I knew I'd found mine.

34:35.782 --> 34:38.451
<i>And it's not just about a steady gig.</i>

34:38.451 --> 34:40.369
<i>Finding your number one pushes you</i>

34:40.369 --> 34:43.664
<i>to unlock parts of yourself
you didn't even know you had.</i>

34:49.921 --> 34:51.631
<i>Because everything you do,</i>

34:53.466 --> 34:55.468
<i>you're doing for someone you care about.</i>

34:59.931 --> 35:01.140
"Oh hell."

35:04.102 --> 35:06.229
They're not numbers.

35:06.229 --> 35:08.314
They're letters.

35:12.985 --> 35:15.613
Did one of them kill Sazz?

35:15.613 --> 35:17.698
We're gonna find out.

35:17.698 --> 35:20.409
We're not investigating
Sazz's murder anymore.

35:21.786 --> 35:23.788
We're investigating mine.
